cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about a new dataset for training end-to-end natural language generation systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for generating natural language, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves content selection, which is a common problem in NLP and could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also establishes a baseline on the dataset, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
